<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 6:16PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT
SOUTHWESTERN TAZEWELL COUNTY THROUGH 645 PM EDT...
At 616 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Claypool Hill, or near Cedar Bluff, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Richlands...
Tazewell...
Cedar Bluff...
Amonate...
Claypool Hill...
Cliffield...
and Bandy.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
